docs.lead_paragraph: It has been four decades since Maher Gendy arrived in New York from his native Egypt, yet the memories of his struggles to adjust to a new country, a new city and a new language remain vivid.

docs.abstract: The secretary of state’s decision most likely ends Republicans’ hopes of securing a potentially dominant candidate for the open seat in Kansas, his home state.
docs.snippet: The secretary of state’s decision most likely ends Republicans’ hopes of securing a potentially dominant candidate for the open seat in Kansas, his home state.
docs.lead_paragraph: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo on Monday told Mitch McConnell, the Senate majority leader, that he does not plan to run for Senate in 2020, most likely ending Republicans’ hopes of securing a potentially dominant candidate for the open seat in his home state of Kansas, according to four people briefed on the meeting.

headline.main: Mike Pompeo Is Said to Decide Against Running for Senate in Kansas
headline.print_headline: Pompeo Is Said to Decide Against Run for Senate in Kansas

docs.abstract: Experts urge early identification and referral for treatment, even if a formal diagnosis has not been confirmed.
docs.snippet: Experts urge early identification and referral for treatment, even if a formal diagnosis has not been confirmed.
docs.lead_paragraph: In December, the American Academy of Pediatrics put out a new clinical report on autism, an extensive document with an enormous list of references, summarizing 12 years of intense research and clinical activity. During this time, the diagnostic categories changed — Asperger’s syndrome and pervasive developmental disorder, diagnostic categories that once included many children, are no longer used, and we now consider all these children (and adults) to have autism spectrum disorder, or A.S.D.

headline.main: Early Treatment for Autism Is Critical, New Report Says

docs.abstract: Francine Segan will talk about Modena and its environs at the 92nd Street Y.
docs.snippet: Francine Segan will talk about Modena and its environs at the 92nd Street Y.
docs.lead_paragraph: Modena, and its surroundings in north-central Italy, are known as the home of balsamic vinegar and Massimo Bottura’s highly esteemed Osteria Francescana. But in some circles, the region is famous as “Motor Valley,” where high-end cars, like Ferrari, Lamborghini, Maserati, Ducati and others, are manufactured. The food historian Francine Segan will discuss dining and driving as it pertains to the area during two lectures at the 92nd Street Y, with food to sample, but nothing to test-drive.

headline.main: A Food Historian Discusses Italy’s Motor Valley
headline.print_headline: To Marvel: The Cars and Food Of Italy’s Motor Valley

docs.abstract: Teeling Whiskey’s first spirit made entirely in the city of Dublin is now available in New York.
docs.snippet: Teeling Whiskey’s first spirit made entirely in the city of Dublin is now available in New York.
docs.lead_paragraph: As Irish whiskey becomes increasingly popular, climbing back up toward to the top-selling position it held 100 years ago, new distilleries are opening at a fast clip. One of them, Teeling Whiskey, established a distillery in Dublin in 2012, and now its first spirit made entirely in the city is available. Other Teeling’s whiskies, which have a history going back to 1782, have been produced in part at family distilleries north of Dublin. The new single pot still whiskey, a honeyed dram both in color and flavor, makes for rich sipping, on the rocks in early evening or later or straight up to mellow the mood after dinner.

headline.main: A Single Pot Irish Whiskey Comes to America
headline.print_headline: To Sip: Single Pot Irish Whiskey  Comes to America

docs.abstract: New York Fed and academic researchers found that U.S. consumers and companies have borne the brunt of the president’s trade war.
docs.snippet: New York Fed and academic researchers found that U.S. consumers and companies have borne the brunt of the president’s trade war.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — American businesses and consumers, not China, are bearing the financial brunt of President Trump’s trade war, new data shows, undermining the president’s assertion that the United States is “taxing the hell out of China.”

headline.main: American Consumers, Not China, Are Paying for Trump’s Tariffs
headline.print_headline: Americans Paying the Price of Trump’s Tariffs
